{
  "_comment": "Article-package pass 2 (writer). Takes one article spec from the picker plus the operator long-form voice samples and the report context. Writes the finalized article body in markdown. The runner calls this pipe once per spec. The operator system prompt (voice profile, long-form samples, structure rules) and user prompt (spec + report context) are injected via the webhook payload at runtime. See packages/apps/market-analysis/prompts/articles.ts for the prompt builders.",
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "webhook_1",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "name": "Web Hook",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 0,
          "y": 440
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "parse_1",
      "provider": "parse",
      "name": "Parser",
      "config": {},
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 230,
          "y": 420
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "tags",
          "from": "webhook_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "question_1",
      "provider": "question",
      "name": "Question",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "question": "You will receive a JSON payload with two fields: \"prompt\" (your task instructions, including the operator system prompt with voice profile and long-form samples, plus the user prompt with the article spec and report context) and \"data\" (a structured copy of the same). Follow the prompt instructions exactly. Respond with ONLY a raw JSON object as specified in your system instructions. No markdown fences, no preamble."
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 472,
          "y": 476.1666666666667
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "text",
          "from": "parse_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "article_writer",
      "provider": "agent_crewai",
      "name": "Article Writer",
      "config": {
        "instructions": [
          "You are the article writer. Your full operator identity, positioning, audience, hard rules, voice profile, long-form voice samples, article structure rules, and the JSON output contract are supplied in the user prompt under the \"prompt\" field at runtime.",
          "Read the article spec in the payload and write the full article body in markdown. Follow the section pattern: opening (no header), context, body sections, worked example, optional honest limit, what-to-do recommendations, runtime reveal at the close, cross-reference inline links, and a Resources footnote when external sources informed the post.",
          "Respond with ONLY a raw JSON object: {\"title\": \"...\", \"subtitle\": \"...\", \"content_md\": \"...\"}. No markdown fences, no preamble, no commentary. Inside the content_md string escape literal double-quotes as \\\" and literal newlines as \\n so the outer JSON parses cleanly. Do not include the title or subtitle inside content_md; they go in their own fields."
        ],
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 702,
          "y": 460.6666666666667
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "question_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_anthropic_1",
      "provider": "llm_anthropic",
      "name": "Anthropic",
      "config": {
        "profile": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "claude-sonnet-4-6": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_ANTHROPIC_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 550,
          "y": 670
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "article_writer"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "response_answers_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "name": "Return Answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 940,
          "y": 470
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "article_writer"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
